Quote:  <i>Braceman</i>: A man employed on the brace where the cages were loaded and unloaded. He had to remove and tip the full trucks and replace them with empties as they arrived in the cage, and had to load men and materials going down the shaft.
Notes:  (Glossary of Waihi Mining Terms)
